ath.basename(file)` for `structural`/`responsibility_cohesion` keys (`file::{detector}::{basename}`), discarding directory context.","Repositories with repeated filenames (e.g., multiple `index.py`/`__init__.py`) can be forced into a shared cluster/action even when concerns are unrelated.","Cluster operations in plan handlers assume cluster membership is meaningful; polluted membership degrades queue focus and remediation planning."],"suggestion":"Change file-scoped grouping keys to use normalized relative paths (or stable path hashes), and keep basename only for display labels. Add a regression test with two different directories sharing the same filename to ensure they do not co-cluster.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"auto_cluster_overreach"},{"dimension":"design_coherence","identifier":"stale_cluster_bypasses_rerun_gate","summary":"Auto-generated stale-review cluster action instructs forced reruns that bypass queue-drain safeguards.","related_files":["desloppify/engine/_plan/auto_cluster.py","desloppify/app/commands/review/preflight.py","desloppify/app/commands/review/entrypoint.py"],"evidence":["`auto_cluster_findings` builds stale action as `desloppify review --prepare --dimensions ... --force-review-rerun`.","`review_rerun_preflight` explicitly bypasses backlog blocking when `force_review_rerun` is set.","This creates a built-in path to rerun subjective cycles while objective/subjective backlog is still open, matching the batch’s workflow-integrity risk hypothesis."],"suggestion":"Remove `--force-review-rerun` from auto-generated cluster actions by default; only suggest it behind an explicit override state (e.g., `plan.allow_forced_rerun=true`) and print backlog counts with a warning before allowing bypass.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"auto_cluster_overreach"},{"dimension":"design_coherence","identifier":"review_pipeline_duplicate_paths","summary":"Review result import/merge flow is duplicated across primary and replay paths, increasing drift risk.","related_files":["desloppify/app/commands/review/batches.py","desloppify/app/commands/review/batch.py","desloppify/app/commands/review/runner_helpers.py"],"evidence":["`batches.py::do_run_batches` performs collect -> merge -> provenance -> write merged file -> import -> optional follow-up scan.","`batch.py::do_import_run` reimplements a near-identical pipeline manually for replayed runs, with parallel parsing/merge/import logic.","Behavior changes to one path can silently diverge from the other (coverage metadata, provenance fields, import semantics, follow-up triggers)."],"suggestion":"Extract a single shared replay-safe pipeline (e.g., `merge_and_import_from_batch_outputs(...)`) used by both normal and import-run flows, with one contract for provenance, coverage metadata, and optional follow-up scan.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"review_orchestration_drift"},{"dimension":"design_coherence","identifier":"inconsistent_next_command_contract","summary":"`review --prepare` emits conflicting recommended next commands depending on code path.","related_files":["desloppify/app/commands/review/prepare.py","desloppify/app/commands/review/batch.py"],"evidence":["`prepare.py::do_prepare` sets `next_command` to include `--scan-after-import`.","`batch.py::_load_or_prepare_packet` sets `next_command` without `--scan-after-import` for packet snapshots.","Both write packet/query guidance, so users and automation can receive inconsistent workflow contracts from equivalent preparation steps."],"suggestion":"Centralize next-command construction in one helper shared by both prepare paths, with explicit policy flags for when `--scan-after-import` is required.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"single_edit","root_cause_cluster":"review_orchestration_drift"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["`auto_cluster_findings` has accumulated multiple policy concerns (grouping semantics, action generation, plan mutation) without clear boundaries.","Review orchestration evolved via additive paths (normal run vs replay) instead of a single reusable pipeline contract.","Prompt/prepare/run metadata responsibilities are split across modules with duplicated string-policy logic."],"likely_symptoms":["auto_cluster_basename_collision","stale_cluster_bypasses_rerun_gate","inconsistent_next_command_contract"],"possible_false_positives":["design_concern:app/commands/review/prepare.py","design_concern:app/commands/scan/scan_reporting_analysis.py"]}}


